cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving Neural Machine Translation (NMT) performance using a semi-parametric approach that combines non-parametric retrieval-based methods with neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of local phrase-level similarities, which could also place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
